// java platform independent

1. we write source code code.java
2. then the code.java is compiled with compiler 'javac'
3. it is converted to byte code 'code.class'
4. the byte code is platform independet code
5. the byte code code.class can be run into any platform with help JVM tool 'java' 
6. then the code.class is converted to executable code for respective platform which is platform dependent

